summary: Hey here is my ENB i guess i dont know if its performance realism or fantasy oh well i guess you can look at the pictures :D
descriptionHtml:
[color=#ff0000](( Installation ))
[/color]
[color=#0000ff]1. get the enb v.262 and put the d3d9.dll and the ENBhost files in your skyrim folder
2. put the "Clear ENB" in the skyrim folder 
3. done i guess :P
[/color]
[color=#ff0000](( required mods ))
[/color][color=#ff7700]Climates of tamriel
[/color][color=#ffff00]RLO

[/color][color=#ff0000](( ini tweaks ))[/color]
[color=#0000ff] make sure your inis is set like this
 
[/color][color=#00ff00]fGamma=1.1000
iMaxAnisotropy=1
bFloatPointRenderTarget=1
bShadowsOnGrass=1
iBlurDeferredShadowMask=3
iWaterMultiSamples=0
iMultiSample=0
bFXAAEnabled=0
bTreesReceiveShadows=1
bDrawLandShadows=1
bDrawShadows=1
[/color]
[color=#ff0000][[ thats about it now you can use the ENB :D ]]

[/color]Credits.
Boris for the ENBseries
and  [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/1005590]CandyRay[/url]
for the DoF
